WEBVTT

00:01.506 --> 00:04.790
You are listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

00:05.291 --> 00:14.322
For more information about First Baptist, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWN.org.

00:14.342 --> 00:17.506
Today's message comes from senior pastor, Dr. Bob McCartney.

00:18.627 --> 00:22.512
Let's open our Bibles this morning to Matthew chapter 6 verse 19.

00:24.455 --> 00:30.482
We've been walking through a series of messages about walking into the valley and sometimes

00:30.658 --> 00:34.242
There are different kinds of valleys this morning.

00:34.282 --> 00:39.507
We're going to talk about the valley of financial problems or financial distress.

00:39.587 --> 00:42.350
And so we're going to talk about when the bank account is empty.

00:42.851 --> 00:44.132
And we need to explore that.

00:44.172 --> 00:47.716
We need to understand some things about walking through this kind of valley.

00:48.317 --> 00:57.266
Since 1967, the publishers clearing house sweepstakes had sort of become a part of a American culture.

00:57.442 --> 01:22.700
Typically on Super Bowl Sunday, the folks from Publishers Clearing House, which was a magazine sales sort of company, they would show up at someone's house, knock on the door, big bouquets of helium balloons and a big oversized check to tell them they had won a considerable sum of money, maybe perhaps hundreds of thousands or later millions of dollars that they would be given through this sweepstakes.

01:23.361 --> 01:27.026
Well, about 15 years ago, they changed how they did that.

01:27.170 --> 01:33.898
And they changed it to a lump sum to $5,000 a week for the rest of your life.

01:34.800 --> 01:36.001
And that sounded pretty good.

01:36.462 --> 01:38.724
That's $260,000 a year.

01:38.764 --> 01:43.490
But however old you were, you got $5,000 a week for the rest of your life.

01:43.971 --> 01:52.882
And that was great until this past January when publishers clearing house declared bankruptcy and

01:53.250 --> 02:00.340
They had no money to pay out the for the rest of your life sums that were supposed to be given to people.

02:02.764 --> 02:09.513
John Wiley, who is 61 years old, says that he won the sweepstakes when he was 51, 10 years ago.

02:10.034 --> 02:13.519
And now he's unemployed, he's looking for a job at 61.

02:14.120 --> 02:15.602
Very few people want to hire him.

02:16.002 --> 02:18.146
He says, quote, this feels like a nightmare.

02:18.708 --> 02:21.694
I thought I was going to go on for the rest of my life.

02:22.074 --> 02:25.201
So I didn't really have to worry about money at all.

02:26.123 --> 02:26.864
Here's the facts.

02:27.526 --> 02:31.133
The facts are that all of us are going to go through a period of financial distress.

02:31.393 --> 02:36.744
And whether you won the sweepstakes or not, all of us are going to walk into a financial valley.

02:37.245 --> 02:37.586
Now,

02:37.698 --> 02:41.224
There are a couple of things that I want to talk about this morning before we dig into the text.

02:41.304 --> 02:45.330
First of all, there are some of you who think I am way too young for this message.

02:45.470 --> 02:46.332
I don't have to worry about this.

02:46.452 --> 02:47.914
Mom and Dad, take care of the bills.

02:48.495 --> 02:54.625
I want to give you some principles this morning, especially those of you who are junior high, high school and college students.

02:55.206 --> 03:03.058
If you will start implementing these simple principles in your life, it will be a lot better for you.

03:03.906 --> 03:12.880
The longer you go without doing some of the things I want to show you from the Bible that God tells us to do financially, the harder your life will get.

03:13.861 --> 03:16.505
But for all the rest of you, I'm just going to tell you this.

03:17.286 --> 03:21.633
We live in a culture of TMI, too much information.

03:22.654 --> 03:23.455
I know too much.

03:24.637 --> 03:25.458
You know too much.

03:26.360 --> 03:30.266
I know too much about where you went on vacation, and you know too much about where I went.

03:30.847 --> 03:33.170
I know too much about the new car or the new truck you got.

03:33.538 --> 03:37.882
I know too much about my neighbor's remodeling project.

03:38.042 --> 03:43.368
We just know way too much about everybody else, and we have this competitive spirit.

03:43.408 --> 03:47.071
There is this desire in our flesh to keep up.

03:47.732 --> 03:51.395
We got to have what everybody else gets.

03:52.456 --> 03:58.723
In my hobby, when one of my friends in cycling or triathlon gets a new bike, I really need one.

03:59.423 --> 04:02.226
I really, really need one.

04:02.466 --> 04:06.731
It's not sort of like there's this joke that says if your wife is angry, go buy a new bike.

04:07.933 --> 04:10.075
She's not going to be less angry, but you'll have a new bike.

04:12.799 --> 04:17.184
Well, we live in a culture that says you've got to keep up.

04:18.285 --> 04:25.394
And because of that, we find ourselves sometimes really struggling financially.

04:26.082 --> 04:30.248
There is a passage of Scripture in which Jesus is going to speak directly to us.

04:30.669 --> 04:34.835
He's going to speak directly into this valley of financial distress.

04:35.576 --> 04:37.399
And we want to talk about that this morning.

04:37.499 --> 04:40.223
It's in the Sermon on the Mount, the greatest sermon ever preached.

04:40.924 --> 04:51.439
Jesus talked about a number of things, but he talked about our relationship, the relationship between God and money and where we have to prioritize that.

04:51.920 --> 04:55.986
So let's look at verse 19 of Matthew chapter six.

04:56.386 --> 04:59.089
And I'm going to point out some verses for you.

04:59.170 --> 05:19.676
First of all, verse 19, do not store up for yourselves treasures on earth where moth and rust destroy where thieves break in and steal, but store up for yourselves treasures in heaven where neither moth nor rust destroys and where thieves do not break in and steal.

05:20.276 --> 05:24.722
For where your treasure is, there your heart will be also.

05:25.250 --> 05:26.512
Skip down to verse 24.

05:28.134 --> 05:39.189
No one can serve two masters, for either he will hate the one and love the other, or he will be devoted to one and despise the other.

05:40.030 --> 05:43.675
You cannot serve God and will.

05:44.596 --> 05:46.258
For this reason I say to you,

05:46.786 --> 05:58.645
do not be worried about your life as to what you will eat or what you will drink nor for your body as to what you will put on is life not more than food and the body more than clothing.

05:59.506 --> 06:06.838
Look at the birds of the sky and they do not sow nor reap nor gather into barns and yet your heavenly Father feeds them.

06:07.739 --> 06:10.383
Are you not much more important than they?

06:10.423 --> 06:14.610
And which of you by worrying can add a single

06:15.138 --> 06:17.200
a single day to his life span.

06:17.661 --> 06:19.383
And why are you worried about clothing?

06:19.823 --> 06:21.605
Notice how the lilies of the field grow.

06:21.665 --> 06:24.308
They don't labor and they don't spend bread for cloth.

06:24.629 --> 06:30.095
Yet I say to you that not even Solomon in all his glory was clothed himself like one of these.

06:30.876 --> 06:37.403
But if God so closed the grass of the field, which is alive today and tomorrow is thrown into a furnace, will he not much more clothe you?

06:38.284 --> 06:39.666
You of little faith.

06:40.386 --> 06:42.930
do not worry then saying, what are we to eat?

06:42.990 --> 06:43.731
What are we to drink?

06:43.771 --> 06:45.033
What are we to wear for clothing?

06:45.814 --> 07:00.916
For the Gentiles eagerly seek all these things, and your heavenly Father knows that you need all these things, but seek first His kingdom and His righteousness, and all these things will be provided for you.

07:01.878 --> 07:07.506
So let's talk about what the Bible tells us about financial faithfulness,

07:07.650 --> 07:10.894
and how to deal with a financial downturn.

07:11.335 --> 07:22.530
When you find yourself in the valley, sometimes people find themselves in the valley because the government shuts down and they're employed by the federal government and they missed a couple of paychecks.

07:22.630 --> 07:23.792
That's pretty tough for people.

07:24.413 --> 07:30.321
Sometimes it happens to people because their company moves and they didn't want to move with their company.

07:30.761 --> 07:37.170
Sometimes it's because of the tremendous cost of some sort of health challenge in their lives.

07:37.570 --> 07:47.023
And so there are a lot of different reasons that we experience difficulties in our financial life, but there are five biblical principles that I want to give you today that are important.

07:47.864 --> 07:57.116
If you are in my college audience, if you're in my high school, if you're my young adult audience even, these five principles are absolutely essential for you.

07:57.817 --> 08:00.341
But if you're older, you can still get it right, okay?

08:00.741 --> 08:01.983
You can start today to get it right.

08:02.343 --> 08:03.445
Here's principle number one.

08:03.645 --> 08:07.250
When it comes to your finances, dedicate it all

08:07.490 --> 08:11.775
to God, dedicate everything you have to God.

08:12.556 --> 08:14.098
It is all His.

08:15.359 --> 08:17.101
He is the owner of everything.

08:17.121 --> 08:18.823
I am a steward.

08:19.744 --> 08:20.685
I don't own anything.

08:20.746 --> 08:25.051
Now, I know according to my deed, I own a house.

08:25.271 --> 08:27.954
According to the title, I own a car.

08:28.935 --> 08:31.338
But in God's economy, here's the truth.

08:32.079 --> 08:33.400
He owns everything.

08:33.440 --> 08:34.802
I don't own anything.

08:35.586 --> 08:42.617
But he has given me the privilege of stewarding or managing some resources, some possessions.

08:42.637 --> 08:50.749
And I want to re- I want to manage those in a way that they are dedicated to his glory and to advancing his kingdom.

08:51.290 --> 08:52.872
I dedicated all to God.

08:53.874 --> 08:56.498
In verse 19, he says to us,

08:56.674 --> 09:10.400
Don't store up for yourself treasures on earth where moth and rust destroy with these break in steel, but store up for yourselves treasures in heaven, dedicate everything you have to God for where your treasure is, there your heart will be.

09:11.442 --> 09:14.688
See, wherever your treasure is, your heart will follow.

09:15.570 --> 09:16.612
Your heart always follows it.

09:16.632 --> 09:17.534
Some people get that backwards.

09:17.554 --> 09:19.698
They think that treasure follows heart.

09:20.034 --> 09:21.196
That's not what Jesus said.

09:21.656 --> 09:27.024
Jesus said that wherever your treasure is, then your heart actually follows.

09:27.464 --> 09:35.356
So if I say all that I have, all of my treasure, all of my earthly possessions, don't belong to me, Lord, they belong to you.

09:36.657 --> 09:38.420
Then my heart begins to follow that.

09:39.141 --> 09:42.125
And my supreme affection is no longer for my stuff.

09:42.666 --> 09:43.527
It's for my savior.

09:44.348 --> 09:47.272
My supreme affection is no longer for the things of this world.

09:47.593 --> 09:48.434
It is for

09:48.770 --> 09:52.955
God who has given his son to die on a cross so that I could have eternal life.

09:53.335 --> 09:57.880
It is for God who has provided me with all of these blessings in my life.

09:58.440 --> 10:02.765
In verse 24, Jesus says, no one can serve two masters.

10:03.786 --> 10:11.575
Now that word is simply drawn from the ancient world where there were people who owned other people, where there were slave owners.

10:12.315 --> 10:15.359
And he says, you can only serve one master.

10:15.959 --> 10:18.482
And God is to be our ultimate

10:18.626 --> 10:21.249
Master, He is the one that we are to serve.

10:21.369 --> 10:23.411
And then Jesus comes to this salient point.

10:23.712 --> 10:28.057
He's like, if I'm not making this plain enough to you, let me just tell you how it is.

10:28.938 --> 10:33.222
You cannot serve God and wealth.

10:34.023 --> 10:36.266
Some older translations use the word mammon there.

10:36.306 --> 10:40.551
It's an old word that just means wealth, means possessions, material things.

10:41.432 --> 10:45.656
And Jesus says, you cannot serve God and wealth.

10:45.676 --> 10:47.218
You're going to serve somebody.

10:48.162 --> 10:51.986
And you're either going to serve God or you're going to serve your stuff.

10:52.947 --> 10:53.908
Let me tell you what I know.

10:55.110 --> 10:58.613
I have learned some of these lessons in my life by living them the wrong way.

11:00.035 --> 11:05.821
Money makes a great servant, but it is a cruel master.

11:07.123 --> 11:13.810
If you live your life for possessions and for stuff and for material gain, I'm going to tell you there is

11:14.114 --> 11:22.123
There is a drumbeat of more, more, more that enters our souls and it consumes us.

11:23.284 --> 11:27.810
But wherever your treasure is, that's where your heart is going to go.

11:28.771 --> 11:30.613
I read an interesting article about a gadget.

11:31.113 --> 11:33.256
I would basically disagree with about a lot of stuff.

11:33.696 --> 11:35.799
His name is Yvonne Schunard.

11:36.419 --> 11:42.386
He is the founder of the really very popular brand Patagonia.

11:42.978 --> 11:45.802
They make all the outdoor stuff and make hiking gear.

11:45.862 --> 11:49.949
They make, you know, ski stuff, all that sort of stuff for the outdoors.

11:50.650 --> 11:55.036
Well, Yvonne Schunard is committed to two things, which is interesting.

11:55.457 --> 11:58.862
Number one, he is a deeply committed socialist.

11:59.583 --> 12:04.912
Now, it's interesting that he built a $3 billion company on capitalism, but he's a socialist, but that's another sermon.

12:04.952 --> 12:06.514
I'm not even going to go there, okay?

12:08.194 --> 12:10.998
but he is also deeply committed to the environment.

12:11.258 --> 12:19.230
So much so that he took the entire $3 billion value of Patagonia and he put it in a trust.

12:19.710 --> 12:28.282
He still draws a salary, but all the rest of the profits and the resources of Patagonia go to saving the environment.

12:28.763 --> 12:31.106
Now, look, I'm all for stewarding the environment, okay?

12:32.008 --> 12:33.930
But here's what he's done.

12:34.691 --> 12:36.594
He's made the environment his God.

12:37.538 --> 12:41.143
And so he's devoted everything he has to the environment.

12:42.325 --> 12:51.979
Now, while I would disagree with his cause and his method, what I would say to you is, that's actually what God calls us to do with him.

12:52.019 --> 12:57.187
To say, God, I'm devoting everything that I am and everything that I have to you.

12:57.247 --> 12:59.070
Lord, it is all yours.

13:00.332 --> 13:03.797
If you're a follower of Jesus, I just want to encourage you to do something.

13:04.618 --> 13:07.442
At some point today, tomorrow in your quiet time,

13:08.002 --> 13:26.245
One of the things you should just do is you ought to have a prayer of dedication, maybe with your family, where you say, Lord, everything we have, our house, our cars, our clothes, the plans we have for how we're going to spend the money, it all belongs to you.

13:27.266 --> 13:30.810
You call the shots with the money that you've given us.

13:31.651 --> 13:37.138
I'm going to tell you that is the first step to financial freedom when the finances are low.

13:37.762 --> 13:41.247
Number two, give the first part to God.

13:42.369 --> 13:44.132
Give the first part to God.

13:44.172 --> 13:48.699
He tells us to seek first the kingdom of God.

13:49.880 --> 13:53.766
See, the first part of what you have should be given to God.

13:56.410 --> 14:00.557
I have tried to live my life for the last few years with a single mantra.

14:00.577 --> 14:03.141
And by the way, after the first service, I said this in the first service.

14:03.621 --> 14:06.706
And a 70-year-old man came up to me and he said this,

14:06.946 --> 14:08.508
He said, Bob, you've said that before.

14:08.648 --> 14:15.637
I heard you say it 10 years ago, but I want you to know that that line changed the whole way that I looked at my finances.

14:16.678 --> 14:17.579
Here's the truth.

14:19.722 --> 14:24.288
Not everything that comes to me is for me.

14:26.531 --> 14:31.597
Not everything that God pours into my life is for my consumption.

14:32.979 --> 14:35.602
God blesses me at times.

14:36.034 --> 14:41.179
so that I will bless others, so that I will advance his kingdom.

14:41.980 --> 14:43.261
Now, how should I give?

14:43.281 --> 14:46.345
Well, the Bible gives us some prescription for that.

14:47.005 --> 14:51.950
In Proverbs chapter three, verse nine, the Bible says, honor the Lord from your wealth.

14:53.392 --> 14:58.757
Honor the Lord from your wealth and from the first of all your produce.

14:59.658 --> 15:03.442
So your barns will be filled with plenty and your vats will overflow with new wine.

15:03.842 --> 15:06.404
First of all, he says, make giving a priority.

15:07.185 --> 15:12.410
You give to God the first fruits of your labor, not the leftovers.

15:12.430 --> 15:20.318
You give to God and you say, God, since I've dedicated it all to you, I'm going to give to you before I give to anything else.

15:20.398 --> 15:23.821
Before I do anything else, I'm going to give you your portion.

15:24.842 --> 15:28.586
Secondly, he says, give a proportion of your income to God.

15:29.346 --> 15:33.010
You need to pre-determine your generosity level.

15:33.506 --> 15:34.908
And you need to budget for that.

15:35.389 --> 15:38.033
But let me tell you where I start.

15:38.053 --> 15:40.477
I believe the Bible teaches the tithe.

15:40.938 --> 15:46.687
Now the tithe is an old English word that the Bible actually clarifies exactly what it means.

15:47.308 --> 15:48.910
You don't get to make it up, okay?

15:49.591 --> 15:54.699
You can say, I think that's Old Testament, I'm gonna give by grace, wonderful, that's fine.

15:55.220 --> 15:59.687
But I believe that the Bible prescribes for us a tithe.

16:00.027 --> 16:01.650
Leviticus 27, verse 30.

16:02.370 --> 16:09.201
Thus all the tithe of the land, the seed of the land, or the fruit of the tree, it is the Lord's.

16:09.782 --> 16:11.024
It is holy to the Lord."

16:11.044 --> 16:12.306
So what does that word tithe mean?

16:12.326 --> 16:13.287
Here it is verse 32.

16:13.928 --> 16:21.861
For every tenth part of herd or flock, whatever passes under the rod, the tenth one shall be holy to the Lord.

16:23.243 --> 16:24.385
Tithe means tenth.

16:25.467 --> 16:27.049
Let me explain at my house.

16:29.133 --> 16:30.034
I have a salary.

16:30.818 --> 16:35.744
And we take the salary and we move it one decimal point to the left.

16:36.866 --> 16:40.210
And that's what we give to start with in our giving.

16:40.451 --> 16:41.512
That's our starting point.

16:42.193 --> 16:45.057
We give proportionally by giving the tithe.

16:46.058 --> 16:52.286
I believe there is a blessing in obedience and I will guarantee you there is a blessing in generosity.

16:53.748 --> 16:57.193
Being generous has its own set of blessings.

16:57.373 --> 16:58.354
Jesus said,

16:58.882 --> 17:02.948
It is more blessed to give than to receive.

17:03.949 --> 17:06.193
Look, Christmas is coming.

17:06.233 --> 17:10.839
Those of us who are parents, I only just want to ask you to answer for yourself a simple question.

17:12.682 --> 17:16.768
Think back to when you were a child and you opened that prized Christmas gift that you wanted.

17:17.890 --> 17:21.074
Maybe it was that BB gun, you know, like Ralphie in a Christmas story.

17:22.837 --> 17:23.357
You opened that.

17:23.738 --> 17:24.740
Now there was joy in that.

17:25.320 --> 17:26.482
Now I want you to fast forward.

17:27.938 --> 17:30.482
to when your child unwrapped a Christmas gift.

17:32.044 --> 17:34.027
Which one brought you the most joy?

17:34.828 --> 17:36.150
It's a no-brainer for me.

17:37.693 --> 17:48.529
Watching my child open Christmas gifts brought me far more joy than the happiness that I got from getting a gift.

17:48.549 --> 17:51.313
It really is more blessed to give than to receive.

17:52.115 --> 17:57.042
And I would challenge anyone when you get your first job

17:57.186 --> 18:10.627
even if it is a summer job when you're a high school student, or it's your job in college, or it's that first job right out of college, or when you get out of high school, start giving to the Lord as a priority and proportionally.

18:11.188 --> 18:13.431
And I would also say this, give it practically.

18:14.233 --> 18:18.680
You need to give and be generous to the kingdom work of God through His church.

18:18.760 --> 18:21.083
There are other great ministries that do wonderful things.

18:21.264 --> 18:25.330
I would advocate for you to give to them, absolutely.

18:25.794 --> 18:26.936
We don't want to be selfish.

18:26.976 --> 18:27.817
It should be hoarders here.

18:27.837 --> 18:32.042
But what we do want to say is this, that good things are happening here.

18:32.103 --> 18:34.005
You're being spiritually fed here.

18:34.686 --> 18:36.488
Your children are being ministered to here.

18:36.769 --> 18:39.312
We're reaching the nations here by going on mission.

18:39.693 --> 18:43.858
And when that happens, you ought to support that as a follower of Jesus through your local church.

18:44.659 --> 18:46.842
So give the first part to God.

18:47.523 --> 18:50.487
Number three, save for the future.

18:51.449 --> 18:52.530
Now, this is something

18:53.026 --> 18:57.994
that I just want to talk to you about as a pastor and try to give you some pastoral wisdom.

18:59.556 --> 19:04.483
The average American household has more debt than savings.

19:06.146 --> 19:08.409
We, and some people have absolutely none.

19:08.449 --> 19:10.553
You have no margin in your life whatsoever.

19:11.193 --> 19:15.139
When Jesus said, don't store up for yourself treasures on earth.

19:15.200 --> 19:18.785
He wasn't saying, don't be prudent and save.

19:20.127 --> 19:22.130
The Bible advocates

19:22.370 --> 19:23.131
for saving.

19:23.652 --> 19:25.275
Saving is wisdom.

19:25.856 --> 19:27.418
It is not unbelief.

19:28.520 --> 19:36.072
Proverbs 21-20, listen to this, in the house of the wise are stores.

19:36.573 --> 19:43.685
They've saved up choice, food and oil, but a foolish man devours all that he has.

19:44.927 --> 19:47.090
When you live a life

19:47.362 --> 19:57.878
of consuming absolutely everything or using everything that comes in and everything that comes in then goes out and there is no plan for saving.

19:59.160 --> 20:03.127
The Bible draws a line between wisdom and foolishness there.

20:04.188 --> 20:15.506
And when we do that, we set ourselves up for having no margin for error, like a government shutdown or like a health crisis.

20:15.746 --> 20:20.152
or like a sudden change in job status.

20:20.192 --> 20:24.057
Maybe your company moves, you get laid off or difficult times come.

20:25.059 --> 20:30.246
You have no margin for error when you don't have any savings.

20:31.147 --> 20:34.732
Now, saving is not necessarily exciting.

20:35.393 --> 20:37.256
I mean, let's just be honest.

20:37.496 --> 20:42.623
Psychologists have proven that when you spend and you buy something, you get a little dopamine rush.

20:43.564 --> 20:44.786
But saving, you don't get that.

20:45.890 --> 20:46.451
You really don't.

20:47.732 --> 20:52.219
But there is a security when there might be an excitement in spending.

20:52.459 --> 20:55.623
There is a security in savings that is important.

20:56.504 --> 20:58.607
I read one lady's story this past week.

20:59.488 --> 21:00.870
And it was really quite heartbreaking.

21:00.930 --> 21:02.212
My heart went out to her.

21:02.673 --> 21:04.916
I don't use her as an example to belittle her.

21:05.016 --> 21:08.861
I use her as an example to say, this is the kind of pain that people experience.

21:09.462 --> 21:10.884
Her name is LaShonda Palmer.

21:10.944 --> 21:15.570
She's a 23 year old or a 23 year veteran.

21:15.650 --> 21:16.952
of the TSA.

21:17.833 --> 21:19.955
Well, TSA is a government agency.

21:19.975 --> 21:22.018
She hadn't been paid, but she's been going to work.

21:22.058 --> 21:27.164
Now that seemed blatantly unfair to me, but at any rate, she hadn't been paid, but she's been going to work.

21:27.805 --> 21:36.055
But the problem is that she rents an apartment, she's a single mom, her rents due, she's overdrawn in her accounts, but there's no margin in her life.

21:37.336 --> 21:40.961
She says, quote, I don't want to get an eviction notice.

21:40.981 --> 21:44.445
It's not that I don't work for it because I am working for it.

21:44.465 --> 21:45.426
I should have it.

21:46.370 --> 21:50.795
See, those lines give a human face to the wisdom of the Bible about saving.

21:51.876 --> 21:54.359
I would say this to any person.

21:55.440 --> 22:08.895
I don't know what you think you can't live without, but even if it is your $5 Starbucks, could you skip that a few days a week and start saving just a little?

22:10.257 --> 22:11.378
The Bible says,

22:11.618 --> 22:19.770
In Proverbs 13 verse 11, dishonest money dwindles away, but he who gathers money little by little makes it grow.

22:20.631 --> 22:31.167
You might be amazed how over the course of a year, you begin to build up a fund that could be your proverb, it could be your proverbs fund.

22:31.968 --> 22:36.816
And when something goes wrong, you've got some money there and you're not living a marginalized life.

22:37.476 --> 22:41.202
See, I am convinced that living a marginalized life is not walking by faith.

22:42.402 --> 22:43.463
It is presumption.

22:44.805 --> 22:47.048
It is poor planning on our part.

22:47.689 --> 22:52.917
And so what we need to do is make sure that even if it is a small amount, we begin to save.

22:53.778 --> 22:56.662
Number four, repay what you owe.

22:57.843 --> 23:08.498
If you have debt, then as a person of integrity, as a follower of Jesus, it is an obligation that we repay what we owe.

23:09.218 --> 23:13.024
Most of our indebtedness comes because we are impatient.

23:14.105 --> 23:15.748
We refuse to wait.

23:16.489 --> 23:18.532
And so plastic is fantastic.

23:18.572 --> 23:20.936
And we go to the mall or we go wherever else it is.

23:21.356 --> 23:24.421
And we begin to accrue high interest credit card debt.

23:25.242 --> 23:32.914
Now, one of the things that we do in our church is we teach Dave Ramsey's curriculum on, uh, on financial freedom.

23:33.378 --> 23:36.143
And we embrace that.

23:36.303 --> 23:43.695
And one of the things that a lot of people don't understand is there is a difference between an expense and an investment.

23:45.337 --> 23:47.781
See, a lot of you were not taught that in school.

23:47.862 --> 23:53.030
I don't know why we're not teaching this in school anymore, but there is a difference between an expense and an investment.

23:53.771 --> 23:55.234
Your house is an investment.

23:56.756 --> 24:00.402
You may be in debt for your house, but it's going to appreciate in value

24:00.770 --> 24:04.296
And that's something that's going to be an investment in your life.

24:04.456 --> 24:13.231
And expense is something that you consume, either immediately like food or over a short period of time like clothing.

24:14.193 --> 24:20.784
We need to make sure that we're not going into debt for expenses, but it's okay for an investment.

24:20.864 --> 24:22.887
That just makes good sense.

24:23.628 --> 24:26.994
But here's something, a principle you need to remember, Proverbs 22, verse seven.

24:27.362 --> 24:33.570
the rich rules over the poor and the borrower becomes the lender's slave.

24:34.751 --> 24:46.846
You see, when I find myself in debt, what I have done is I have found myself in the position of a servant to that lending company, to that credit card company.

24:47.227 --> 24:54.616
And whatever portion of my income is, that is indentured to them, that's then enslaved to them.

24:55.077 --> 24:56.178
Then here's what I can't do.

24:57.122 --> 25:01.326
I can't use that to glorify God.

25:01.867 --> 25:03.969
I can't even use that to provide for my family.

25:05.310 --> 25:09.835
Every dollar you spend on interest is a dollar.

25:10.435 --> 25:19.564
You cannot spend either to advance the kingdom of God and the gospel or to enjoy for your family.

25:19.584 --> 25:21.506
That leads me to the fifth principle.

25:23.248 --> 25:25.330
Enjoy what you have.

25:26.050 --> 25:39.545
A lot of sermons on stewardship on financial faithfulness kind of end with the point four, but I want to end with point five because I believe it is an act of gratitude to enjoy the blessings of God.

25:40.506 --> 25:54.322
When you dedicated all to him, when you give the first portion back to him to advance his kingdom through his church, when you begin to save prudently for times when maybe things happen that are out of your control,

25:54.754 --> 26:02.382
And when you are on a mission to get rid of your debt, then whatever remains, enjoy it.

26:03.243 --> 26:05.145
Enjoy the life that God has given you.

26:06.187 --> 26:23.986
In 1 Timothy, chapter 6, the apostle Paul wrote these words, instruct those who are rich in this present world, not to be conceited or to set their hope on the uncertainty of riches, but on God dedicated all to Him.

26:25.314 --> 26:33.082
on God who richly supplies us with all things to enjoy.

26:34.924 --> 26:36.406
Now, that's a biblical principle.

26:37.747 --> 26:47.638
There is absolutely nothing wrong with the enjoyment that comes from being able to provide for our families.

26:47.798 --> 26:48.699
It's Christmas time.

26:49.520 --> 26:50.121
Go shopping.

26:51.262 --> 26:53.785
Now, make sure you get the first four points in order.

26:53.825 --> 26:55.026
Don't go into debt to do it.

26:56.226 --> 26:57.067
But go shopping.

26:57.308 --> 26:57.929
Buy gifts.

26:58.790 --> 27:01.594
Some of you are blessed to have a place in Colorado.

27:01.614 --> 27:02.135
Go skiing.

27:03.157 --> 27:04.679
Or you're going to rent a place in Colorado.

27:04.699 --> 27:05.600
Go skiing at Christmas.

27:05.701 --> 27:06.121
It's great.

27:06.422 --> 27:07.143
It's fantastic.

27:07.543 --> 27:09.166
Enjoy the blessings of God.

27:10.027 --> 27:11.129
Enjoy what He's given.

27:11.149 --> 27:13.052
It is an act of gratitude.

27:14.694 --> 27:22.226
This past summer, we got to go to the beach, my favorite place.

27:22.370 --> 27:26.676
One morning, I just went out, I did a little run, and I was standing there at the beach.

27:27.778 --> 27:30.562
And I just spent a moment, and I said, God, thank you.

27:31.544 --> 27:33.246
Thank you to get to be in this beautiful place.

27:33.286 --> 27:35.429
Thank you that I get to enjoy.

27:35.449 --> 27:36.531
Thank you for blessing me.

27:37.452 --> 27:41.919
It's an act of worship to enjoy the blessings of God.

27:43.301 --> 27:51.954
Granger Smith was a country music singer, by the way, started picking guitar and singing when he was a student at Texas A&M University.

27:52.386 --> 27:59.396
And he was kind of Texas country for a while, and then he went to Nashville and he had a recording contract.

28:00.257 --> 28:03.081
But in 2019, he had a horrible tragedy in his life.

28:04.964 --> 28:08.228
He and his wife lost a three-year-old son in a drowning accident.

28:08.248 --> 28:09.670
It was horrible, obviously.

28:10.451 --> 28:12.714
For the next four years, Granger said he really struggled.

28:13.716 --> 28:19.984
And finally, in 2023, he just decided that country music was no longer where he needed to be.

28:20.445 --> 28:21.106
As a matter of fact,

28:21.666 --> 28:30.015
stopped touring, canceled all his future tour dates that I'm not recording another album, left Nashville and enrolled in seminary.

28:31.317 --> 28:32.778
And now he is a pastor.

28:34.220 --> 28:39.906
He's a pastor serving God, and he doesn't make the kind of money that he made singing country music.

28:40.907 --> 28:46.834
But he said this in an interview, I had everything people chase.

28:47.810 --> 28:49.512
I thought that was an incredible experience.

28:49.532 --> 28:55.918
I had everything that people chase, what we're pursuing, and I was still empty.

28:57.160 --> 29:05.008
Now I drive my kids to school, I'm on the yard, I study God's Word, and I've never had more peace.

29:07.110 --> 29:11.414
Enjoy what you've been given.

29:11.434 --> 29:14.898
You've been listening to a message from First Baptist Church, which is not false.

29:15.234 --> 29:24.259
For more information about First Baptist, including gathering times and locations, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWF.org.

29:24.279 --> 29:25.522
We'll see you next week.

